# Full Platform API & Schema Documentation

This document outlines the Database Schemas (Models) and the RESTful API Endpoints available for the Switch2iTech frontend application.

---

## 🏗️ 1. Database Schemas (Models)

### 1.1 User ([/models/user.js](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/models/user.js))
Role-based user model managing auth and profile details.
* `_id`: ObjectId
* `name`: String (Required)
* `email`: String (Required, Unique)
* `password`: String (Hashed)
* `profile`: String (Cloudinary URL)
* `role`: Enum `["user", "admin", "client", "developer", "manager"]` (Default: "user")
* `phoneNo`, `company`, `address`: String
* `assignedProjects`: Array of [Project](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/projectController.js#89-104) ObjectIds
* `skills`: Array of Strings (For developers)
* `isVerified`, `isEmailVerified`, `isPhoneVerified`: Boolean
* `emailVerificationCode`, `phoneVerificationCode`: String
* `verificationCodeExpires`: Date
* `loginOtp`: String
* `loginOtpExpires`: Date
* `lastLogin`: Date

### 1.2 Project ([/models/project.js](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/models/project.js))
High-level overview of a commissioned project.
* `_id`: ObjectId
* `title`: String (Required)
* `description`: String
* `coverImage`, `demoVideo`: String (Cloudinary paths)
* `status`: Enum `["planning", "active", "on-hold", "in-review", "completed", "cancelled"]`
* `priority`: Enum `["low", "medium", "high", "critical"]`
* `clients`: Array of [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectIds
* `manager`: [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectId
* `teamMembers`: Array of [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectIds (Developers)
* `startDate`, `endDate`: Date
* `budget`: Number, `currency`: String (Default: "USD")
* `tags`: Array of Strings
* `faqs`: Array of `{ question: String, answer: String }`

### 1.3 Milestone ([/models/milestone.js](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/models/milestone.js))
A sub-division of a Project (e.g., Sprint or Phase).
* `_id`: ObjectId
* `title`: String (Required)
* `description`: String
* `project`: [Project](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/projectController.js#89-104) ObjectId (Required)
* `assignedTo`: [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectId (Manager / Lead Developer)
* `status`: Enum `["pending", "in-progress", "completed", "on-hold"]`
* `startDate`, `dueDate`: Date
* `order`: Number (Default: 0)

### 1.4 Module ([/models/module.js](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/models/module.js))
A major feature or logical component within a Milestone.
* `_id`: ObjectId
* `name`: String (Required)
* `description`: String
* `milestone`: [Milestone](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/projectController.js#192-203) ObjectId (Required)
* `project`: [Project](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/projectController.js#89-104) ObjectId (Required)
* `assignedTo`: [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectId (Developer)
* `status`: Enum `["pending", "in-progress", "in-review", "completed"]`
* `dueDate`, `completedAt`: Date
* `order`: Number (Default: 0)

### 1.5 Task ([/models/task.js](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/models/task.js))
Atomic work unit assigned to a developer.
* `_id`: ObjectId
* `title`: String (Required)
* `description`: String
* `module`: [Module](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/projectController.js#274-287) ObjectId (Required)
* `milestone`, `project`: ObjectIds
* `reporter`, `assignee`: [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectIds
* `status`: Enum `["todo", "in-progress", "in-review", "done", "blocked"]`
* `priority`: Enum `["low", "medium", "high", "critical"]`
* `dueDate`, `completedAt`: Date
* `labels`: Array of Strings
* `estimatedHours`, `loggedHours`: Number

### 1.6 Product ([/models/product.js](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/models/product.js))
Pre-built SaaS templates or tools available for purchase/view.
* `_id`: ObjectId
* `name`, `desc`, `category`: String (Required)
* `clients`: Array of [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectIds (Buyers)
* `video`, `image`: Array of Strings (Cloudinary URLs)
* `thumbnail`: String
* `techStack`: Array of Strings
* `faqs`: Array of `{ question: String, answer: String }`

### 1.7 Testimonial ([/models/testimonial.js](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/models/testimonial.js))
Reviews of Projects or Products.
* `_id`: ObjectId
* `author`: [User](file:///d:/Projects/switch2itech/switch2itechWeb/backend/switch2itech-backend/projects-backend/controllers/userController.js#28-39) ObjectId (Required)
* `authorNameOverride`, `authorRoleOverride`, `authorCompanyOverride`, `authorAvatarOverride`: String
* `title`, `content`: String
* `rating`: Number (1-5, Default: 5)
* `project`, `product`: ObjectIds (Reference target of review)
* `isApproved`, `isFeatured`: Boolean

---

## 🌐 2. API Endpoints

**Base URL**: `http://localhost:5000/api` 

> **Authentication**
> Most routes labeled "Private" require a valid JWT passed in as an `httpOnly` cookie (`jwt`). The cookie is set automatically upon login/register.

### 2.1 Auth (`/api/auth`)
* `POST /register`: Register a new user. Expects `name, email, password, [phoneNo, company, address, role]`.
* `POST /login`: Log in via email/password. Expects `email, password`.
* `POST /request-otp`: Request an OTP login code. Expects `identifier` (email or phone).
* `POST /verify-otp-login`: Login using OTP. Expects `identifier, otp`.
* `POST /verify-email`: (Private) Verify email post-registration. Expects `code`.
* `POST /verify-phone`: (Private) Verify phone post-registration. Expects `code`.
* `POST /logout`: (Private) Clears JWT cookie.
* `GET /me`: (Private) Returns the logged-in user profile.

### 2.2 Users (`/api/users`)
* `GET /`: (Admin) Get all users.
* `GET /:id`: (Private) Get a user by ID.
* `PUT /profile`: (Private) Update own profile. Accepts `name, phoneNo, company, address, skills, password, profile (file upload via Multer/Cloudinary)`.
* `PATCH /:id/role`: (Admin) Update a specific user's role. Expects `role`.

### 2.3 Projects (`/api/projects`)
* `GET /`: Get all projects (populated with clients, manager, teamMembers).
* `GET /:id`: Get specific project details, including all its associated Milestones and Modules.
* `POST /`: (Admin/Manager) Create project. Accepts `title, description, status, priority, budget, currency, tags[array], faqs[JSON array string], coverImage (file), demoVideo (file)`.
* `PATCH /:id`: (Admin/Manager) Update project fields.
* `DELETE /:id`: (Admin) Cascade deletes project, milestones, modules, and tasks.
* **Assignments:**
  * `PATCH /:id/assign`: (Admin) Assign stakeholders. Expects `{ clients: [ids], manager: id, teamMembers: [ids], action: "add"|"remove" }`.
* **FAQs:**
  * `POST /:id/faqs`: Add a project FAQ. Expects `{ question, answer }`.
  * `PATCH /:id/faqs/:faqId`: Update project FAQ.
  * `DELETE /:id/faqs/:faqId`: Delete project FAQ.

### 2.4 Milestones (`/api/projects/:projectId/milestones`)
* `GET /`: Get all milestones for a project.
* `POST /`: (Admin/Manager) Create a milestone. Expects `title, description, status, startDate, dueDate`.
* `PATCH /:milestoneId`: (Admin/Manager) Update milestone.
* `DELETE /:milestoneId`: (Admin) Delete milestone (and cascade delete sub-modules/tasks).
* **Assignments:**
  * `PATCH /:milestoneId/assign`: (Admin/Manager) Expects `{ assignedTo: userId }`.

### 2.5 Modules (`/api/projects/:projectId/milestones/:milestoneId/modules`)
* `GET /`: Get all modules for a milestone.
* `POST /`: (Admin/Manager) Create module. Expects `name, description, status, dueDate`.
* `PATCH /:moduleId`: (Admin/Manager/Developer) Update module.
* **Assignments:**
  * `PATCH /:moduleId/assign`: (Admin/Manager) Expects `{ assignedTo: userId }`.

### 2.6 Tasks (`/api/projects/:projectId/milestones/:milestoneId/modules/:moduleId/tasks`)
* `GET /`: Get all tasks within a specific module.
* `POST /`: Create a task. Expects `title, description, status, priority, dueDate, labels, estimatedHours`.
* `PATCH /:taskId`: Update a task. (Status updates automatically trigger notifications).
* `DELETE /:taskId`: (Admin/Manager) Delete task.
* **Assignments:**
  * `PATCH /:taskId/assign`: (Admin/Manager) Expects `{ assignee: userId }`.

### 2.7 Products (`/api/products`)
* `GET /`: List all products.
* `GET /:id`: Get specific product.
* `POST /`: (Admin) Create product. Accepts `name, desc, category, techStack, image (up to 5 files), video (up to 2 files), thumbnail (1 file)`.
* `PUT /:id`: (Admin) Update product details/images.
* `DELETE /:id`: (Admin) Remove product.
* **FAQs:**
  * `POST /:id/faqs`, `PATCH /:id/faqs/:faqId`, `DELETE /:id/faqs/:faqId` (Admin).

### 2.8 Testimonials (`/api/testimonials`)
* `GET /`: List testimonials. Supports queries like `?approved=true`, `?project=<id>`, `?product=<id>`.
* `GET /:id`: Get single testimonial.
* `POST /`: (Private) Submit a review. Expects `content, rating, [title, project, product, overrides...]`.
* `PATCH /:id`: (Private) Update own testimonial.
* `PATCH /:id/approve`: (Admin) Approve/Feature a testimonial (`isApproved, isFeatured`).
* `DELETE /:id`: (Admin) Delete testimonial.
